Refactor client-server websockets

Remove HTTP rest routes for Client-to-server syncs

We had a dual approach to syncing, involving a websocket in one direction and a REST api in the other. We've done away with the REST api, and have set up the codebase to easily reimplement client-to-server syncs (with Websockets).

Minor fixes
Initial work on proper MakeDrive client API

Updated filer-fs module listing in package.json

"Filer-fs" hasn't been published to NPM, so we are installing directly from the git repository. I updated the link to point at the master branch of the remote repo.
Buffer implementation for makedrive
Fix rsync 32 bit checksum algorithm
Fixed a unit test bug regarding uploading files

Added an auth solution for websockets

Until we figure out how to intercept the HTTP get request that is upgraded into a websocket, we will be using a token-based system to indicate that a websocket can be trusted. Anyone can open a websocket with the server with this approach, but only authenticated users will be able to get a token allowing them to use it.
Fix for client can't connect to the websocket

Added server-to-client socket unit tests, with util methods

Most of the work here was in setting up the util module to make testing syncing over a socket, and connecting to a socket, easier. The exact mechanics of this will change as our spec does, but the changes to the test suite will be minor compared to if this patch was never done.
